text:
Just a summary of things to research/think about this week in regards to the project idea we spoke about tonight:

1. Define Requirements:
• Identify the core features we want for fitness app (e.g., tracking meals, workouts, setting goals).
• Specify the user roles and their permissions (e.g., regular user, admin).
• Determine the external API(s) we want to integrate (e.g., nutrition data, workout routines).
2. Front End  (React):
• Create user interfaces for different features using React components.
• Implement React Router for navigation between different pages.
• Connect to the backend using API calls to perform CRUD operations.
• Implement user authentication and authorization.
3. Back End  (Java/Spring Boot):
• Set up Spring Security for user authentication and authorization.
• Create RESTful APIs for CRUD operations on different entities (e.g., users, meals, workouts).
• Connect to MySQL database using Spring Data JPA for data persistence.
• Integrate external API(s) for additional data (e.g., nutrition information).
4. User Account Management:
• Implement user registration and login functionality.
• Allow users to reset their passwords.
• Create user profiles with personalized information.
5. External API Usage:
• Integrate external API(s) to fetch nutritional data for meals.
• Use external API(s) for workout recommendations or exercise details.
• Display external API data in a user-friendly manner within app.
6. CRUD Functionality:
• Implement CRUD operations for key entities (e.g., meals, workouts).
• Allow users to track their daily intake and exercise routines.
• Provide a history or log page to view past entries.
7. Additional Features (Beyond Required Specs):
• Social Integration: Allow users to connect with friends, share achievements, or challenge each other.
• Progress Tracking: Implement charts and graphs to visualize user progress over time.
• Notification System: Send reminders or notifications for user goals, achievements, or daily tracking.
• Meal Planning: Provide a feature for users to plan meals in advance and generate shopping lists.
• Weather API: Axios/Postman to fetch API data on weather for the day. Render components to tell you if it's a good day for a run!
8. Testing:
• Write unit tests for both front end and back end components.
• Conduct integration testing to ensure seamless communication between the front end and back end.
9. Miscellaneous:
• Deploy application on a cloud platform (e.g., AWS, Heroku).
• Set up continuous integration and continuous deployment (CI/CD) pipelines.
• Document code, API endpoints, and project structure.
• Provide a user guide for app.
• Security: Implement secure coding practices, validate input, and protect against common vulnerabilities.
• Scalability: Design application with scalability in mind, considering potential future enhancements.
